# gen179 — B5 for-loop: parrot0 runs the three-clause `for (init; cond; post)`,
# desugared to init + while(cond){ body; post }, including i++/i-- in the post.
# Same step ceiling as while.
#expect: pass
#faculty: symeval-for
> what does sum(4) return: int sum(int n) { int s = 0; for (int i = 1; i <= n; i = i + 1) { s = s + i; } return s; }
< sum(4) returns 10
> what does fact(5) return: int fact(int n) { int r = 1; for (int i = 2; i <= n; i++) { r = r * i; } return r; }
< fact(5) returns 120
> what does sq(4) return: int sq(int n) { int s = 0; for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) { s = s + n; } return s; }
< sq(4) returns 16
